# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Injinary Wallet — Publishing credentials
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in the values. `.env` is gitignored.
#
# These credentials are consumed by `wxt submit` (which wraps
# `publish-browser-extension`). They are only needed when publishing — local
# dev and `wxt build` work without any of them.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ─── Chrome Web Store ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Setup: https://developer.chrome.com/docs/webstore/using-api
#
# 1. Create a project in Google Cloud Console: https://console.cloud.google.com
# 2. Enable the "Chrome Web Store API".
# 3. Create OAuth 2.0 Client ID credentials (type: "Desktop app").
# 4. Use the client_id to get a refresh_token via the one-time OAuth flow:
#      https://accounts.google.com/o/oauth2/auth?response_type=code&access_type=offline&scope=https://www.googleapis.com/auth/chromewebstore&client_id=<CLIENT_ID>&redirect_uri=urn:ietf:wg:oauth:2.0:oob
#    Authorise, copy the code, then exchange it:
#      curl "https://oauth2.googleapis.com/token" \
#        -d "client_id=<CLIENT_ID>&client_secret=<CLIENT_SECRET>&code=<CODE>&grant_type=authorization_code&redirect_uri=urn:ietf:wg:oauth:2.0:oob"
#    The response contains the refresh_token.
# 5. Upload the extension manually once via https://chrome.google.com/webstore/devconsole
#    to obtain the EXTENSION_ID.
CHROME_EXTENSION_ID=
CHROME_CLIENT_ID=
CHROME_CLIENT_SECRET=
CHROME_REFRESH_TOKEN=

# ─── Firefox Add-ons (AMO) ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Setup: https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/developers/addon/api/key/
# Optional — only fill in if you publish to Firefox.
FIREFOX_EXTENSION_ID=
FIREFOX_JWT_ISSUER=
FIREFOX_JWT_SECRET=

# ─── Edge Add-ons ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Setup: https://learn.microsoft.com/microsoft-edge/extensions-chromium/publish/api/using-addons-api
# Optional — only fill in if you publish to Edge.
EDGE_PRODUCT_ID=
EDGE_CLIENT_ID=
EDGE_CLIENT_SECRET=
EDGE_ACCESS_TOKEN_URL=
